BGP Lab with iBGP and eBGP Topology (GNS3)

## Overview
This lab demonstrates Border Gateway Protocol (BGP) configuration
using both iBGP (Internal BGP) and eBGP (External BGP) on GNS3
with Cisco IOS routers.

## Topology
- Multiple Autonomous Systems (AS)
- eBGP between different AS routers
- iBGP between routers within the same AS
- Route advertisement and path selection

## Protocols Used
- eBGP (External BGP)
- iBGP (Internal BGP)
- BGP route advertisement

## Tools Used
- GNS3 Simulator
- Cisco IOS Routers

## Key Concepts Practiced
- BGP neighbor relationships (eBGP & iBGP)
- AS numbers configuration
- Network advertisement via BGP
- BGP table verification using show ip bgp
- Ping tests across autonomous systems

## How to Open
1. Install GNS3 on your PC
2. Import BGP2.gns3 file
3. Start all devices
4. Verify BGP neighbors with:
show ip bgp summary
show ip bgp
show ip route bgp

